TypeScript uses a configuration file, named tsconfig.json, that holds a number of compilation options. 
So basically you can configure the TS compilation on this file.

To generate tsconfig.json
tsc --init

tsconfig.json:

target: --> Tells JavaScript version that we would like to generate for.


In order to compile a TypeScript project that may contain many files in many sub-directories, we just need to type tsc in the root directory of the project.


watching the files for change: tsc -w